# Fitness Tracker App Structure

This is a React Native/Expo fitness tracking app that integrates with Strava and Hevy APIs.

## Core Architecture

- **Entry Point**: [App.tsx](mdc:App.tsx) - Main navigation setup with 3 screens
- **Configuration**: [src/config/api.ts](mdc:src/config/api.ts) - API keys and configuration
- **Environment**: Uses `.env` file for API keys (hidden from git)
- **Theme**: [src/styles/theme.ts](mdc:src/styles/theme.ts) - Dark theme with iOS-style design

## Key Components

- **WorkoutCalendar**: [src/components/WorkoutCalendar/WorkoutCalendar.tsx](mdc:src/components/WorkoutCalendar/WorkoutCalendar.tsx) - Smart calendar with Strava/Hevy integration
- **StravaAuth**: [src/components/StravaAuth/StravaAuth.tsx](mdc:src/components/StravaAuth/StravaAuth.tsx) - OAuth authentication component
- **HomeScreen**: [src/screens/HomeScreen/HomeScreen.tsx](mdc:src/screens/HomeScreen/HomeScreen.tsx) - Main calendar view

## API Services

- **StravaService**: [src/services/stravaService.ts](mdc:src/services/stravaService.ts) - Strava API with caching and rate limiting
- **HevyService**: [src/services/hevyService.ts](mdc:src/services/hevyService.ts) - Hevy API integration

